Problem 3

Here I compared the founded column to the rating column. Maybe the year a company was founded has to do with its overall rating. I used a scattero=plot for this data.

jobs %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Founded, y = Rating )) +
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 660 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

I’m not seeing much correlation here (and I’m assuming you’re not either), but two things occur to me that might improve this a little: (1) I feel like the -1 ratings are probably NA values; let’s remove them, and (2) Let’s try adding an alpha (transparency setting) to see if we’re getting overplotting on the far right side:

jobs %>%
  filter(Rating > -1) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Founded, y = Rating )) +
  geom_point(alpha = .4) 
## Warning: Removed 408 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

(The alpha is definitely helping–there is overplotting on the right.) It might also be worth skipping over those very early founded companies (of which there are a very small number).
